snippet.textDisplay:
I worked with the art department of a marketing and advertising agency in the past and we discussed a lot 'bout the things you have to consider when developing any content towards a smartphone. In my country, most people buy budget phones, the ones of 400U$ and below, and it is very comon to use the smartphone dimmed to save battery. Not a very high quality screen to start of and not a very large battery aswell.


My point is, to actually have a good experience with HDR on youtube using your phone, the brightness have to be crancked up to maximum. It makes it very unconfortable when using in darker enviroments and increase the battery consunption. Overall, I think most people wont notice the difference at all. So ya, there is my overrated tech of the year :P

snippet.textDisplay:
Senate Concurrent Resolution (SCR) No. 6 was voted on by the Missouri House of Representatives on May 15, 2019, making the resolution officially passed by the Missouri State Legislature.

SCR 6 calls on “the Chinese Government to end the practice of organ harvesting from prisoners as well as prisoners of conscience, specifically Falun Gong prisoners of conscience.”

While previous versions of this resolution were passed by the Missouri House of Representatives in 2017 and the Missouri Senate in 2018, it must be voted on by both the Senate and House within the same 5-month legislative session to be finalized as a concurrent resolution.
snippet.textOriginal:
Senate Concurrent Resolution (SCR) No. 6 was voted on by the Missouri House of Representatives on May 15, 2019, making the resolution officially passed by the Missouri State Legislature.

SCR 6 calls on “the Chinese Government to end the practice of organ harvesting from prisoners as well as prisoners of conscience, specifically Falun Gong prisoners of conscience.”

While previous versions of this resolution were passed by the Missouri House of Representatives in 2017 and the Missouri Senate in 2018, it must be voted on by both the Senate and House within the same 5-month legislative session to be finalized as a concurrent resolution.

snippet.textDisplay:
When i saw a comment saying this was 8k i was like "nah man thats stupid!", my 1440p display(which is high end by most peoples standard) cant see that difference. Neither should there be a big difference from 4k monitors seeing 8k video. But i decided to test it out anyways!

And to my surprize i actually can see the difference. From 1080p to 1440p the diff is huge so much loss of detail especially when you are moving(im guessing YT downgrade). But even up to 4k i see more and more details on stills and better detail preservation when you were moving. And at 8k i got even more detail. Like the pores of your nose was like attacking me!
Im pretty sure i have good eyesight so i might be quite alone, but i felt like the jump from 1440p-4k was the same as 4k-8k. Just the starting point was so much better from 4k-8k but there was still a big difference in amount of detail.
